# Python Patterns -- LinkedIn Autopilot V2

## Type Hints
- Add type hints to all public function signatures
- Use `Optional[X]` or `X | None` for nullable params
- Use `dict[str, Any]` over `Dict[str, Any]` (Python 3.11+)

## Docstrings
- Every module, class, and public function gets a docstring
- Use Google-style docstrings (Args, Returns, Raises)
- Agent classes document: purpose, inputs, outputs, schedule

## Testing
- Use pytest, test files in `tests/`, named `test_*.py`
- Manual testing: `python main.py --run <team>`
- Mock Claude API calls in tests (never spend real tokens in tests)

## Imports
- Standard library first, third-party second, local third
- Use absolute imports over relative
- Common imports: `anthropic`, `yaml`, `requests`, `apscheduler`

## Error Handling
- Catch specific exceptions, never bare `except:`
- Use `logging` module, not `print()`
- Log with `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`
- Classify errors: FATAL (stop pipeline) vs RETRYABLE (retry with backoff)
- Clean up temp files in `finally` blocks

## Agent Pattern
- Inherit from `BaseAgent` (`agents/base.py`)
- Load prompts via `self.load_prompt()` from `prompts/` directory
- Access config via `self.config` (loaded from `config/business.yaml`)
- Template variables: `{{owner_name}}`, `{{brand}}`, `{{business_name}}`
- Config resolution: check `config/` first, fall back to `config_examples/`

## Path Handling
- Use `os.path.join()` or `pathlib.Path`, never string concatenation
- Project root: `os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))`
- Data directory: `data/` (gitignored)
- Config directory: `config/` (gitignored), templates in `config_examples/`

## Async / Scheduling
- APScheduler for cron jobs (`scheduler.py`, `scheduler_engagement.py`)
- No hardcoded timezones -- read from config
- Use `--dry-run` before wiring into schedulers
- No unauthorized cron job modifications without approval

## API Clients
- Anthropic client initialized in `BaseAgent` with `CLAUDE_MODEL` env var
- Default model: `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`
- Never hardcode API keys -- always `os.getenv("KEY_NAME")`
- Check for API key existence at startup, fail fast if missing

## f-strings
- Prefer f-strings over `.format()` or `%` formatting
- Example: `f"Processing {agent_name} at {datetime.now()}"` not `"Processing {} at {}".format(agent_name, datetime.now())`

## No Mutable Defaults
- Never `def foo(items=[])` -- use `def foo(items: list | None = None)`
- Initialize inside function body: `items = items or []`
